All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Bank
The Bank class simulates a bank that can serve only one client at a time.
City
Singleton class representing the city, containing all banks, workers, and spenders.
Client
Abstract class representing a city client (either Worker or Spender).
ConfigLoader
Singleton configuration loader that reads simulation parameters from properties files.
EntityFactory
Factory interface for creating simulation entities (Banks, Workers, and Spenders).
HelpDesk
Singleton help desk service providing assistance information for the city simulation.
Logger
Utility class for logging messages to the console.
Main
Main class for running the city economic simulation.
Media
Media is a daemon thread that periodically prints and logs the state of the city (banks, workers, spenders).
Spender
The Spender class models a spender who hires workers and pays them a salary.
Utils
Utility class for random selection and filtering operations in the city simulation.
Worker
The Worker class models a worker who can be hired by only one spender at a time.
